HEADWORD: Subreligion
<hw>Sub`re*li"gion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A secondary
religion; a belief or principle held in a quasi religious
veneration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Loyalty is in the English a <qex>subreligion</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

